				<p><p>Do you mean too close to each other?</p>

<p>It sounds like you might be referring to the sorts of steering behaviours that Craig Reynold's refers to in his <a href="http://www.red3d.com/cwr/boids/" rel="nofollow">Boids project</a>. He describes some behaviours that exhibit as <em>flocking</em> or <em>herding</em> because of the way the participants avoid each other, yet stick together.  He uses the terms 'separation', 'alignment' and 'cohesion' to describe the algorithms involved. </p>

<p>Craig applies these to computer simulations, but you could just as well apply the concepts to robots.</p>

<p>Other searches that may prove beneficial: 'flock simulation', 'crowd modelling'.</p>
